stories.title: 'The worst England tour ever'
stories.seoTitle: I Was There: West Indies 5-0 defeat of England in 1985-86
stories.summary: Thirty years ago England were battered, bruised, broken and blackwashed in the Caribbean

image.caption: Ian Botham is caught behind by Thelston Payne off Malcolm Marshall
image.longCaption: Ian Botham is caught behind by Thelston Payne off Malcolm Marshall, West Indies v England, 2nd Test, Port-of-Spain, 4th day, March 11, 1986

stories.title: The bouncer's impact
stories.summary: The life-threatening injury suffered by Phillip Hughes is a reminder of the dangers faced by batsmen when handling bouncers. Here, three Test batsmen recall how they were impacted by injuries arising from short balls.

image.caption: Mike Gatting is hit by a bouncer by Malcolm Marshall
image.longCaption: Mike Gatting is hit by a bouncer by Malcolm Marshall, West Indies v England, 1st ODI, Jamaica, February 18, 1986

stories.title: WEST INDIES v ENGLAND 1985-86
stories.subTitle: First One-day International
stories.summary: A bad injury to Gatting, whose nose was broken when he missed an attempted hook off Marshall from a ball which cannoned off his face into the stumps, did far more damage to England than West Indies' easy victory
